  "description": "I\u0026rsquo;m going to see if I can\u0026rsquo;t get TAB installed today. I did =git clone https://github.com/gaz561/tab= and then =make tab-bin= as the index.md instructed. Got an error about lacking Lua - makes sense, the README said it was necessary. Trying =sudo apt install lua= prompted me to pick between a version, 5.1 to 5.4. No memory what TAB used, so I went for 5.4.\nDid a =make clean= to try and clean things up, but I noticed it did leave directories behind. =make tab-bin= procueded without error.\n",
